British Petroleum Co PLC'sannouncement that its U.S. subsidiary intends to tender for the45 pct of Standard Oil Co &lt;SRD> it does not already own,catapulted U.S. oil stocks sharply higher this morning, tradersand analysts said.    "It raises the specter of additional consolidation in theindustry and that is what is boosting the other oils," analystRosario Ilacqua of L.F. Rothschild said.    Sanford Margoshes of Shearson Lehman Brothers said "thisdeal shows that British Petroleum, a conservative investor thatknows the oil business, is clearly confident in the U.S. oilindustry, and that shines well on the U.S. companies." More&#3;